<template><div><h2 id="ğŸ§ -mindset" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#ğŸ§ -mindset"><span>ğŸ§  Mindset</span></a></h2>
<ul>
<li>Intervals represent <strong>a range of values</strong> or <strong>a duration of time</strong> with a defined <strong>start</strong> and <strong>end</strong></li>
<li>Common problem domain
<ul>
<li>Time management (<strong>a time sequence</strong>, find available slot, merge intervals)</li>
<li>Project management (tasks may have <strong>dependencies</strong>, i.e. one task must be finished before another task)</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Possible states for two intervals
<ul>
<li>There is a <strong>gap</strong> between A and B</li>
<li>A <strong>overlaps</strong> B</li>
<li>A <strong>overshadows</strong> B</li>
<li>Reverse of B to A</li>
<li><img src="/assets/image/leetcode/interval.png" alt="interval" tabindex="0" loading="lazy"><figcaption>interval</figcaption></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
